===Etymology===
From Old Northern French {{term|saussiche}} ( = Old and modern French {{term|saucisse}}), from late {{etyl|la}} {{term|salsicia}}, feminine singular form of *{{term||salsicius}}, from {{term|salsus||salted}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/ˈsɒsɪdʒ/}}
* {{audio|en-us-sausage.ogg|Audio (US)}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# A food made of ground meat (or meat substitute) and seasoning, packed in a cylindrical casing. Also a length of sausage, or an example of a sausage.
# A sausage-shaped thing.
# {{colloquial}} [[penis|Penis]].
# A term of [[endearment]]
#: ''my little '''sausage'''''
#: ''Silly '''sausage'''.''

